         <entryFree xml:id="k000139" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">pingliang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">平梁</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">平梁</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin" type="ATTCAT_preferred" source="#biblk000139-1">píngliáng</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">p'ing-liang</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-6" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation" source="#biblk000139-2">level, flat; even; roofbeam, ridgepole (lit.)</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-7" xml:lang="en" type="ATTCAT_preferred_translation" source="#biblk000139-3">level cross beam (ATTCAT preferred translation)</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-8" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000139-4">top beam</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000139-9" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000139-5">two-rafter crossbeam</term>
            <note type="Note (full)">
               <note type="getty:scopeNote" xml:lang="en">
                  <p source="#biblk000139-6">Pingliang refers to <term ref="/keyword/k000045">cross beams</term> that span two <term ref="/keyword/k000107">rafters</term> and are located on the highest layer of the roof frame. This term is used in the <title ref="https://tinyurl.com/36hnkkzs">Yingzao fashi</title>, where it is also called <term>pingfu 平栿</term>. In extant architecture, <term>shuzhu 蜀柱</term> and <term>chashou 叉手</term> are joined into the top of the pingliang (Liang 1983, 142 ; Chen 2010, 114). In official <term subtype="dynasty" ref="https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000070">Qing</term> dynasty architectural terminology, the beam in the location of the pingliang is called <term>sanjialiang 三架梁</term>, meaning a beam that spans three purlins (and two <term ref="/keyword/k000107">rafters</term>), or <term>taipingliang 太平梁</term>.</p>
               </note>
               <note type="getty:scopeNote" xml:lang="zh-Hant">
                  <p source="#biblk000139-6">平梁為《<title ref="https://tinyurl.com/36hnkkzs">營造法式</title>》（1103）所用術語，也稱<term>平栿</term>。指長兩<term ref="/keyword/k000107">椽</term>，位於梁架最上一層的<term ref="/keyword/k000045">梁</term>。現存實例中平梁上通常立<term>蜀柱</term>與<term>叉手</term>（梁 1983, 142；陳 2010, 114）。在<term subtype="dynasty" ref="/keyword/k000070">清</term>官式的梁架及其術語體系中，屋架最上層的<term>太平梁</term>或<term>三架梁</term>與《<title ref="https://tinyurl.com/36hnkkzs">營造法式</title>》平梁相當。</p>
               </note>
            </note>       
